12 Section 1. Section 61-9-419, MCA, is amended to read:
13 "61-9-419. "Properly restrained" defined Definitions. (1) As used in 61-9-420 through 61-9-423
14 and this section, unless the context requires otherwise, the following definitions apply:
15 (a) "Booster seat" means a child safety restraint system that meets applicable federal motor
16 vehicle safety standards and is designed to provide belt-positioning that elevates a child to be properly seated
17 with a safety belt.
18 (b) "Child safety restraint system" means a device that:
19 (i) meets applicable federal motor vehicle safety standards; and
20 (ii) is appropriate to the age of the child being restrained, as provided in 61-9-420.
21 (c) (i) "properly restrained" "Properly restrained" means fastened in a manner prescribed by the
22 manufacturer of the child safety restraint system that permits the child safety restraint system to act as a body
23 restraint, but.
24 (ii) The term does not mean a system in which the only body restraint is a safety belt of the type
25 required by 61-9-409.
26 (d) "Secured with a safety belt" means restrained or secured by a seat belt that:
27 (i) meets applicable federal motor vehicle safety standards; and
28 (ii) is properly adjusted and fastened, including both the shoulder and lap straps, when equipped
