3 Section 2. Section 61-9-420, MCA, is amended to read:
4 "61-9-420. Child safety restraint systems -- standards -- exemptions. (1) Each motor vehicle
5 passenger who is under 6 years of age and weighs less than 60 pounds must be transported and properly
6 restrained in a child safety restraint. The child safety restraint must be appropriate for the height and weight of
7 the child as indicated by manufacturer standards. A motor vehicle passenger who is under 2 years of age must
8 be properly restrained in a rear-facing child safety restraint system that complies with federal motor vehicle
9 safety standards.
10 (2) A motor vehicle passenger who is between 2 years of age and up to 4 years of age must be
11 properly restrained in a rear-facing or forward-facing child safety restraint system with an internal harness that
12 complies with federal motor vehicle safety standards.
13 (3) A motor vehicle passenger who is between 4 years of age and up to 8 years of age must be
14 properly restrained in a forward-facing child safety restraint system with an internal harness or a child booster
15 seat that is secured with a vehicle lap-shoulder seat belt, whichever is applicable, that complies with federal
16 motor vehicle safety standards.
17 (4) A motor vehicle passenger who is at least 9 years of age or has outgrown the height or weight
18 limits of a child booster seat as set by the manufacturer, whichever comes first, must be properly restrained
19 with a motor vehicle adult safety belt.
20 (5) A child safety restraint system pursuant to 61-9-419 through 61-9-423 must be installed,
21 adjusted, and used according to the manufacturer instructions.
22 (2) The department shall by rule establish standards in compliance with 61-9-419 through 61-9-
23 423 and applicable federal standards for approved types of child safety restraint systems.
24 (3) (6) The department may by rule exempt from the requirements of subsection (1) this section a
25 child who because of a physical or medical condition or body size cannot be placed in a child safety restraint
26 system."
